1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 c5
{ c5 is a very popular choice. It is known as the Open Variation because the position is more likely to open up as trades occur in the center. }
4. Ngf3 { White develops. } 4... Nc6
{ Black puts more pressure on the center. } 5. exd5
{ White can later put pressure on Black's center pawns. } 5... exd5 6. Bb5
{ Now Black has two choices. } 6... Qe7+
{ This is an interesting move to sneak in. However, the queen on e7 will block in the bishop on f8. }
7. Be2
{ White is not worried about captures on d4 because they doubled isolated pawns that are created will be very weak. }
7... Nf6 8. O-O Qc7 { Black frees his bishop on f8. } 9. Re1 cxd4 10. Nb3
{ White will win back the d4-pawn next with a good position. } *

