{ White can later put pressure on Black's center pawns. } 5... exd5 6. Bb5
{ Now Black has two choices. } 6... Bd6
{ Developing the bishop is perfectly logical, but now White can force the creation of an isolated pawn. }
7. dxc5 Bxc5 8. O-O { Now Re1 is coming. } 8... Ne7 9. Nb3
{ White's knights are prepared to leap to d5 any moment. } 9... Bd6
{ Black's bishop retreats to d6. } 10. Re1 O-O
{ Black side-steps any annoyances along the e-file. } 11. Bd3 h6
{ A nice little defensive move. } 12. h3 { Bg4 would be quite annoying. } 12...
Nf5 { Black increases the activity of his knights. } 13. c3
{ White prevents any Nd4 ideas by Black. } 13... Qf6 14. Bc2
{ White prepares Qd3. } 14... Rd8 15. Qd3 g6 { White cements the f5 knight. }
16. Bd2
{ White has a decent advantage and can put pressure on Black's isolated d-pawn. }
