1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 Nc6
{ The Guimard Defense is a bit of a surprise weapon, but White can achieve a large advantage if he knows how to handle it. }
4. Ngf3 Nf6 5. e5
{ White closes the position, and Black's knight is inconveniently placed on c6, where it blocks the c-pawn. Usually Black would want to play c5 soon but here that is not possible due to the knight on c6. }
5... Nd7 6. Bd3 { White is developing normally. } 6... f6
{ This is the alternative to Nb4, undermining the e5-pawn. } 7. Ng5
{ This is a clever tactical idea that puts Black under immediate pressure. Now fxe5 runs into Nxe6 and Black is lost. }
7... Ndxe5 { Black has no choice. Everything else leads to trouble. } 8. dxe5
{ White takes the knight. } 8... fxg5 9. Qh5+
{ White's attack is coming fast. } 9... g6 10. Bxg6+
{ White takes advantage of the rook on h8. } 10... Kd7 11. c4
{ A thematic move, ripping open the position and exposing the Black king. }
11... Nxe5 12. Bc2 { White does not want to give away the bishop. } 12... Qf6
13. O-O { Black is up a pawn but his position is still very uncomfortable. } *

